The Nigeria Football Federation (NFF) has dismissed rumours that Feyenoord forward Cyriel Dessers is set to be called up to the Super Eagles African Cup of Nations (AFCON) 2021 squad as a potential replacement for Odion Ighalo. The Belgium-born forward was touted to stand in for Ighalo as the ex-Watford attacker may not be able to represent Nigeria at the AFCON as his Saudi Arabia-based club Al-Shabab will not release him due to contractual issues. Before joining the White Lion from Shanghai Shenhua in 2021, the 2019 AFCON top scorer signed a clause that he would not be involved in international duties.   Akpeyi, Noble fancy Eagles chances     BetKing to fly five fans to watch AFCON finals     Covid chaos stop Senegal flight to Cameroon   Prior to that move, Ighalo had announced his retirement from the Nigeria national team, however, he was recalled by Gernot Rohr as the German moved to solve the Super Eagles’ worrisome attacking line. Dessers was a surprise omission initially, having scored nine goals and recorded two assists in 21 games for Feyenoord this season. - Advertisement - But a top official with the NFF revealed that no player that has been included in the 28-man squad can be replaced unless there is an injury in the team. “No Dessers. We can’t change, we can only change on health grounds,” a top official in the NFF revealed to NationSport.